[/asy] The final Answer is 5.8
 ### Proof
 Since the smaller square has a perimeter of 4 cm and its sides are equal in length, each side measures $4/4=1$ cm. Since the larger square has area 16 square cm, each side measures $\sqrt{16}=4$ cm.
